data.title: based Injury Statistics Query and Reporting System
data.meta_description: Web-based Injury Statistics Query and Reporting System
data.meta_site_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention
data.text:
Find data for fatal injuries due to homicide, suicide, and deaths of undetermined intent that may have been due to violence, legal intervention deaths, and unintentional firearm deaths.

Visualize the impact of injury-related deaths in the United States compared to other leading causes of death or find the impact of premature death resulting from injury compared to other leading causes of premature death.

Stay up to date with the most recent fatal injury data available. Find the number of deaths due to unintentional injury such as drowning, falls and motor vehicle crashes by month and year including the most recent provisional data available.

Find the medical cost for injury deaths in addition to cost associated with lives lost.
